""
"As a proud polish immigrant son, I was really excited to see a polish beer style I didn't know existed.  I was happy with the beer, but non-plussed overall.  Good black malt flavor and some mellow smoke.  Light body and easily drinkable overall.  This beer was made for regional tastes and big pours, and it reflects.  In the modern american brewing landscape of one offs and limited batches, it sadly fails to impress when beer geeks expect a blast of this or that.  As an overall experience, it was basically a schwarzbier with a touch of bacon.  Nowhere near a rauchbier, maybe if there was a line between schwarzbier and rauchbier, this would be 25% rauchbier from the schwarzbier side.  If you released this in the 80's, it would blow minds and put your brewery on the map, but in the modern age of wild ales and 13% bourbon stouts, it fails to register for citizenship in crazytown."
