"I've missed this one a few times at a few local places, so it was serendipitous that I'd find it here at Tap House as part of this beastly Lips of Faith takeover thing. That and Svengoolie. Love it. Anyway, this stuff pours a sorta/kinda murky smoke ash topped by a finger or so of, well, ashen foam. The nose comprises oak smoke, light wood, clove, and a vague sense of cracked wheat in the distance. The taste brings in more of the same, the smoke taking a strong lead, but then the underlying slightly-sour wheat comes in near and through the finish, mixing with the smoke in a fairly enjoyable manner. It's never fully seamless, but it still mostly works. The body is a light medium, with a light moderate carbonation and a fluid feel. Overall, a nice bit of wheaty smoke. 'Nuff said."
"O - Again, can't speak to style, but this beer is a bit too astringent for my tastes. Could be nice paired with a big plate of ribs slathered with a sweet BBQ sauce, or with a fuller bodied, sweeter malt bill. It may not be to style, but maybe there's a reason this style died."
